    "text": [
        "Dear Mr. John,",
        "I am writing this letter regarding Java course that I am attending in the evening slot around 6:30 p.m.",
        "At present, I am working 9 hours a day in my office from Monday to Friday and Post my office work in the evening attending the Java class for 2 hours and then leaving to home. Once I reach my house, I am focusing on finishing my pending activities and then going to bed for sleep. This routine Continued from the past one month.",
        "As described above, I am completely occupied during weekdays and also Personally, I am not having sufficient time to concentrate on any other activities. Looking into the current workload, I may need to extend my office work hours in order to deliver the project on the agreed time. Hence, It is not feasible for me to attend the Java course in the evening time.",
        "At the same time, I do not want to miss learning the course. As an alternative to this, I am interested in Joining the course on the weekends, assuming slots are available to join. It would be helpful for me if you consider my request to attend the class on weekends.",
        "I am looking forward to hearing from you. Thanks for considering my request.",
        "Yours sincerely,",
        "Rajesh."
